description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are seeking a highly motivated cardiac physiologist to join our friendly team, providing high standards of care and support to patients in Hywel Dda University Health Board.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We offer a comprehensive range of cardiac and respiratory investigations including pacemaker implant and follow up, exercise and tilt testing, respiratory tests and ambulatory monitoring. Our echo department delivers both simple transthoracic echocardiography and a range of complex echocardiography techniques such as transoesphageal, contrast, dotutamine and exercise stress echocardiography. In addition, the department delivers a range of diagnostic clinics such as echo surveillance clinics, chest pain assessment and arrhythmia assessment clinics.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are committed to supporting learning and development so a successful candidate should be confident that they will be supported to consolidate their learning and begin to develop expertise. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;All applicants must have BSc Clinical Physiology (cardiology) or equivalent and demonstrate competency in a range of non-invasive procedures. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are seeking a candidate that shares our values and commitment to ensuring the quality of our services. We encourage open engagement in service design and delivery, and seek an individual eager to share knowledge and ideas in an open and friendly forum. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Enquiries to Melanie Haworth or Catrin Williams.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interviews for this post will be held on 20th November 2020.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
